            <abstract id="ref9" encodinganalog="5203_">The Oregon State Tuberculosis Hospital was housed in the buildings of the former Oregon Mute School in Salem, OR. The Hospital began admitting patients in 1910. In 1963 due to increase of patients and the combination of the Hospital in Salem with the University of Oregon Medical School State Tuberculosis Hospital. As a result patients on the Portland campus were transferred to the Salem Hospital. The collection contains reports, Birth Certificate Books, Admissions and Discharges, Scrapbooks, Photographs and Correspondence.</abstract>
